	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You can store as many files as you'd like, but if you have many files in one directory it will take longer to load the ROM list and it will take you longer to find the game you want, like Jeroen said.
<br />
<br />A good idea is to create one folder for each letter ("A", "B", "C", and so on) to store the games that start with the letters, because the PowerPak does not sort the names alphabetically. Another possible way to distribute them even more is creating folders for different game genres ("platform", "fighting", "shooting", and so on).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


